author: philip
msg: Fix part of issue 779.
* subversion/libsvn_subr/io.c (svn_io_run_diff): Treat a return value
of 2 from the diff process as an error.

author: philip
msg: Fix issue 936 by passing a second label to external diff program, from
an idea in a patch from Gustavo Niemeyer <niemeyer@conectiva.com>.  Add
revison information to the labels - we've got it so we may as well print
it!  Fix a bug that caused a file diff to appear twice.
* subversion/include/svn_io.h (svn_io_run_diff): Add second label parameter.
* subversion/libsvn_subr/io.c (svn_io_run_diff): Add second label parameter.
* subversion/svnlook/main.c (print_diff_tree): Pass NULL as second label
to svn_io_run_diff.
* subversion/libsvn_wc/diff.c
(struct edit_baton): Add revnum member.
(set_target_revision): Store revnum in edit baton.
(file_diff): Pass SVN_INVALID_REVNUM as second revision to file_changed.
(delete_entry): Add file path to the directory's hash of already compared
items so that the diff doesn't appear twice.
(close_file): Pass edit baton revision and SVN_INVALID_REVNUM to file
changed callback.
* subversion/libsvn_client/diff.c
(struct diff_cmd_baton): Add revnum1 and revnum2 members.
(diff_label): New function.
(diff_file_changed): Call diff_label twice.
(diff_file_added, deleted): Pass diff_cmd_baton revnums to diff_file_changed.
(do_diff): Change void* baton to struct diff_cmd_baton*. Set revnum1 and
revnum2 in baton.
(svn_client_diff): Initialise revnum1 and revnum2 in baton.
This is an empty revision for padding.
